    <completion-notes>Both PB-017 and PB-022 confirmed STUB-AS-EXPECTED on spaarkedev1. PB-017 (GUID 24051c80-…) has 1 deployed node which has drifted to a bare AI-Analysis placeholder (nodeType=100000000, __actionType=0) — even more inert than the repo stub which defines a createNotification node. PB-022 (GUID be7874be-…) has 1 deployed node "Notify New Assignment" matching the repo stub (actionType=50 with {{task.*}} mustache referencing variables no upstream node produces — inert). Both playbook headers (schedule/parameters/channel) match repo exactly. Both playbooks produce zero notifications today (no query node feeding the template). Neither has LookupUserMembership. Audit report at notes/audit/014-pb-017-022.md instructs task 015 to SKIP both — W1 tasks 024 (matter-activity) + 025 (work-assignments) own end-to-end rewrite + redeploy. Carry-forward note for W1: PB-017's deployed node needs wholesale delete-and-replace (currently an AI-Analysis placeholder, not the createNotification stub from repo).</completion-notes>
  </metadata>

